Deputy Coroner Cushman testified that he had made a post-mortem examination of
                     the body; he found the womb large, and evidence that a fœtus had been expelled;
                     there was a laceration, which was probably produced by some sharp instrument;
                     death, in his opinion, had been caused by metro-peritonitis, the result of an
                     abortion.

